    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Gallbladder management in bariatric surgery is controversially discussed. While some surgeons
      advocate routine prophylactic cholecystectomy (CCE) during Roux-en-Y gastric bypass (RYGB)
      others advocate CCE only in patients with pathological gallbladder findings. The aim of this
      study was to evaluate the necessity of prophylactic CCE in patients receiving a laparoscopic
      RYGB.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
